revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-31 22:02:11.000000000', 'message': 'Abstract 'mv'/'cp' shell commands in guestagent

The guestagent commonly executes basic shell commands
across multiple files and datastores.
Each datastore currently scripts its own shell calls.
Apart from cluttering the Python code with shell constructs,
it also makes maintenance of the shell calls more difficult by
requiring the same change be made across multiple lines,
source files and/or potentially even datastores.

The goal of this patch set is to provide a simple straightforward
interface for most common shell calls used across the guestagent
code while encapsulating the related shell code into a single module.

This patch set includes refactoring of 'mv' and 'cp' calls.
It also introduces unit tests ('guestagent/test_operating_system')
for the above implementations.

The shell code was moved into 'common/operating_system' module.
The replacing interface is:

def move(source, destination, force=False, **kwargs):
    """Move a given file or directory to a new location
    (by default as root).
    Move attempts to preserve the original ownership, permissions and
    timestamps.

def copy(source, destination, force=False, preserve=False,
	 recursive=True, **kwargs):
    """Copy a given file or directory to another location
    (by default as root).
    Copy does NOT attempt to preserve ownership, permissions and timestamps
    unless the 'preserve' option is enabled.

The calls also take optional keyword arguments:
    :param run_as_root:      Execute as root (default).
    :type run_as_root:       boolean

    :param timeout:          Number of seconds if specified,
                             default if not.
                             There is no timeout if set to None.
    :type timeout:           integer

Change-Id: Ib969a111d102b817c9f18437c1f36bd17e3a8a4b
Closes-Bug: 1438430
Related-Bug: 1431618

commit_message:
Abstract 'mv'/'cp' shell commands in guestagent

The guestagent commonly executes basic shell commands
across multiple files and datastores.
Each datastore currently scripts its own shell calls.
Apart from cluttering the Python code with shell constructs,
it also makes maintenance of the shell calls more difficult by
requiring the same change be made across multiple lines,
source files and/or potentially even datastores.

The goal of this patch set is to provide a simple straightforward
interface for most common shell calls used across the guestagent
code while encapsulating the related shell code into a single module.

This patch set includes refactoring of 'mv' and 'cp' calls.
It also introduces unit tests ('guestagent/test_operating_system')
for the above implementations.

The shell code was moved into 'common/operating_system' module.
The replacing interface is:

def move(source, destination, force=False, **kwargs):
    """Move a given file or directory to a new location.
    Move attempts to preserve the original ownership, permissions and
    timestamps.

def copy(source, destination, force=False, preserve=False,
	 recursive=True, **kwargs):
    """Copy a given file or directory to another location.
    Copy does NOT attempt to preserve ownership, permissions and timestamps
    unless the 'preserve' option is enabled.

The calls also take optional keyword arguments:
    :param as_root:          Execute as root.
    :type as_root:           boolean

    :param timeout:          Number of seconds if specified,
                             default if not.
                             There is no timeout if set to None.
    :type timeout:           integer

Change-Id: Ib969a111d102b817c9f18437c1f36bd17e3a8a4b
Depends-On: Idbfa05fdc5c48aed31989578f828a7f57aca3be2
Closes-Bug: 1438430
Related-Bug: 1431618

commit_message:
Fix os_region_name in provider

Commit e6e8f6a56231409028ff1e7cdcd44781ca37d5b0 changed the section
where the os_region_name setting is placed from 'DEFAULT' to
'glance_store'. However, the provider was not updated to reflect
this change, so it broke.

- check-tempest-dsvm-neutron-dvr http://logs.openstack.org/78/163178/4/check/check-tempest-dsvm-neutron-dvr/3bb0aab/ : SUCCESS in 59m 03s (non-voting)'}, {'account_id': 6788, 'date': '2015-03-11 14:54:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

If I understand correctly the problem you are trying to fix is the following:

1) port is on host 1, status is active and port is bound to host 1
2) port migrates to host 2
3) host 2 sends get_device_details and the port status is set to PORT_STATUS_BUILD but the binding is not updated, the port is still bound to host 1
4) host 2 sends update_device_up but the port status is not set to active since the port is not bound to host 2
5) port update is sent to update the host, the port binding is updated but the status stays the same.

Your fix now is not to change the port status to PORT_STATUS_BUILD in point (3). This probably solves the problem but I don't think it's entirely correct. When a port comes up on host 2 it's right to set the status to PORT_STATUS_BUILD, because indeed we are not sure that the port is up, even if most of the times it is. With your fix if the port is down Neutron will never detect that.
The real problem I think is that the port binding should be updated when host 2 sends get_devices_details for the port. When the l2 agent detects a new port sends a get_devices_details, so that's already a sign that the port has migrated, we don't need to wait for the port update from Nova. A better fix for me would be to change the check here [1] . Basically the port should be rebound if the host that requested the details (that is binding.host) is different from the previous one that is binding.original.host 

What do you think?

[1] https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/master/neutron/plugins/ml2/plugin.py#L267"}, {'account_id': 2888, 'date': '2015-03-11 16:57:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Hi rossella, thanks for your review

you're right on the call flow, and if the agent wants to set the status to down, it can't with this patch.So i'm ok with the fact that this patch doesn't resolve bug 1274160.

I'm not sure that rebinding the port on get_device_details would be a solution since the host parameter in get_device_details is not mandatory. This was yamamoto's concern on PS2.
However I'll experiment this kind of patch.

As described in [1], I though a good correction would involve a nova patch.

However this patch fix the issue reported by mike in [2], in the context of HA router port with l2pop.
May be we should create a dedicated bug report for [2] that this patch solves.
Or may be marking this patch with a partial-fix for the bug, since the port is more likely to be in UP state than in BUILD state.

Thoughts?

[1]https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1274160/comments/3
[2]https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1274160/comments/7"}, {'account_id': 6788, 'date': '2015-03-12 10:29:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Hi Mathieu,

thanks for the reply,
I think this patch should fix the bug completely :)
In the current form is not even a partial fix since you are introducing another bug (port DOWN not detected)

If we bind the port during get_device_detail we don't need to wait for the port_update notification from Nova. Do we agree? That would simplify the process a lot.

The host parameter in get_device_detail was introduced in Icehouse. This fix is going to be merged (maybe) in Kilo, so we can assume that the host is set. I don't think we support running agents that are 2 version older than the server, do we?


Thoughts?


If you test it let me know how it goes."}, {'account_id': 2888, 'date': '2015-03-12 16:25:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

after discussing with rossella and rkukura on IRC, it seems that giving the ability for get_device_details to modify the host_id is not a good option : races may occur, especially when migration are triggered by a compute host being down, but recovering during the migration.

commit_message:
ML2: Change port status only when it's bound to the host

Currently, nothing prevents the port status to be changed to BUILD
state when get_device_details() is sent by a host that doesn't own
the port.
In some cases the port might stay in BUILD state.
This could happen during a live-migration, or for multi-hosted ports
such as HA ports.
This commit allows the port status modification only if the port
is bound to the host that is asking for it.

Closes-Bug: #1439857
Closes-Bug: #1438040
Closes-Bug: #1416933

Change-Id: I9b3673f453abbafaaa4f78542fcfebe8dc93f2bb

does it affect CentOS only? what about Ubuntu?'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2015-04-16 13:33:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

As I noticed at the related bug, I cannot reproduce the issue on Ubuntu'}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2015-04-16 13:46:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

So my understanding of this issue when looking in to it is that it only affects CentOS deploys via an image.  The kickstart scripts include a /sbin/chkconfig mcollective on.  The reason why this only affects centos is that defaults for chkconfig within the mcollective init script is set to - so it won't automatically be started when installed.  I believe the Ubuntu packages have the mcollective service start automatically for run levels 3,4,5."}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2015-04-16 13:51:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Also to address Bogdan Dobrelya's question about the removal of cloud-init, I do not believe that the removal of cloud-init via puppet affects this change because the puppet items are run after the initial installation of the image and cloud-init being run. [{'created': '2015-03-31 16:24:53.000000000', 'message': 'Stop using cfg.CONF in unit tests

Using the oslo_config.cfg.CONF global object directly has the
potential to conflict with the lazy-loading of the tempest.config.CONF
instance.  Rather than requiring selective enforcement of this rule -
allowed in unit tests and not everywhere else - this change removes
all use of cfg.CONF outside of tempest.config.

Change-Id: I5210ea4241e58157d72c0dc5551936e5e9cffeb0
'}]
commit_message:
Stop using cfg.CONF in unit tests

Using the oslo_config.cfg.CONF global object directly has the
potential to conflict with the lazy-loading of the tempest.config.CONF
instance.  Rather than requiring selective enforcement of this rule -
allowed in unit tests and not everywhere else - this change removes
all use of cfg.CONF outside of tempest.config.

Change-Id: I5210ea4241e58157d72c0dc5551936e5e9cffeb0

commit_message:
Rename stackforge/murano to openstack/murano

* Move Murano related projects to openstack namespace
* Move murano-docs to stackforge-attics

Repository murano-docs is moved to attics cause we don't use
this repo for storing documentation, our documentation
is stored in stackforge/murano repo.

Approved commit to governance repository:
   https://review.openstack.org/162745

Change-Id: I56dd0fe97b6aec7026e7ff605f2893cd7521ffcf

commit_message:
Remove the tuskar-ui-extras repository from Stackforge

This repository contained extensions for Tuskar-UI specific to the
Red Hat products, such as Satellite support, etc.

We have moved our development to our own repository at
https://github.com/rdo-management/tuskar-ui-extras and will no longer
need the Stackforge repository.

Change-Id: I98e8fe58eb69cd1b9d69b4161060a5ea0d1865f9

commit_message:
Raising errors from the client instead of ksclient

Consolidates HTTPError types into barbicanclient.exceptions.
Provides a uniform way of external consumers to catch
common exceptions that might occur as a result of normal
client operation.

Fixes bug 1431514

Change-Id: Id65e7da913bb06e2f94a50f44550199dc7f1beb6

commit_message:
Fix error in scripts/run-upgrade.sh

This commit simply updates scripts/run-upgrade.sh to fix the typo
where the echo is not actually appending output to user_secrets.yml.

commit_message:
MAC address of VM not getting populated in OVSDB

The patch set fixes the problem described in the launchpad
bug 1445153, where the L2 gateway service plugin was getting
an error while inserting VM MAC address into the OVSDB server
when a new VM is booted on a network for which l2-gateway
connection exists.

Change-Id: I7e84a91f6e37c4bf557f8536b95b91f4a08f427c
Closes-Bug: 1445153

commit_message:
Add action execution ID to action context

With introduction of action execution, for supported action classes, the
action_context passed as input args to the action class during action
execution should include the action execution ID.

Change-Id: I49d88c57aceef92f548f3680980040f78a4cdfb4
Closes-Bug: #1444155

commit_message:
Move neutron-pg-full to periodic

Only 7% of people use postgres in production, and since we cannot test
all the configurations in the check queue and this is a fairly rare
configuration, move it to the nightly periodic-qa queue (and
experimental so it can be manually triggered).

Source: http://superuser.openstack.org/articles/openstack-user-survey-insights-november-2014

periodic-qa reports the results to the mailing list
openstack-qa@lists.openstack.org

Change-Id: I235f6fe1c0f37c8f3acaf92562d2d6320a86483c

commit_message:
Drop neutron-pg  in favor of a voting neutron-pg-full

Now that tempest-dsvm-neutron-pg-full is passing, make it voting and
drop tempest-dsvm-neutron-pg, since its just a subset of full.

Change-Id: I08d423c50d1af3314838b4e9622302346149cc31

commit_message:
Make coverage job voting

Instead of asking people to write unit tests let's just make
coverage job voting.

This can be implemented in very simple maner:

1) checkout to master
2) run coverage and get base line
3) checkout back
4) run coverage to get current coverage
5) If coverage was reduced more then 0.01% mark job as failed

commit_message:
Don't assign any roles to created users by default

Role context may be used if role is required by scenario.

Closes-Bug: #1444916
Change-Id: I558ad934f3f7e60f616985d1b54fe896709eb916

commit_message:
Resolves lookup plugin name duplication issue

The `playbooks/plugins/lookups/py_pkgs.py` had an issue where it's
assumed that the name of a package is always split on an "_" however
a repo name could be anything before the `_git_repo` portion. This
commit corrects that issue.

Change-Id: I49f8a7726ed99e47ff514cdf6e61472fac5b9ed4
Partially-Implements: blueprint master-kilofication

commit_message:
Add order_retry_tasks migration per latest model

After the retry feature was implemented changes were made to the
OrderRetryTask model (in particular extending ModelBase) that added new
attributes to the entity. This CR formally adds those new attributes
via an Alembic migration module.

commit_message:
Reworked Dell SC iSCSI target portal return

On initialize_connection the code to determine the portal, lun and
iqn info to return could skip ports and potentially not return the
best portal choice.  In the case of multipath being enabled not all
ports would be returned.

Also changed a LOG.debug to a LOG.info in initialize_connection.

Closes-bug: 1442346

Change-Id: I2c5235da4d373d15303325a51ed1d4c37fd38815

commit_message:
Use the split out -api and -registry glance packages

Glance packaging for RDO has recently split out the -api and -registry
packages from openstack-glance, so those need to be installed as part of
the overcloud-control element.

commit_message:
Implement baylock in conductor for horizontal-scale

Implements a distributed bay lock to avoid race conditions when
multiple conductors are deployed. A conductor should acquire a lock
when it is about to perform an operation on a bay. The lock
acquisition will succeed if the bay is not currently locked or the
conductor that owned the lock is dead. An ActionInProgress exception
will be raised if the lock acquisition fails.

Change-Id: I055696c43e356dc6fbd03996f1dd28e3c8c41594
Partial-Implements: blueprint horizontal-scale

commit_message:
Resolves lookup plugin name duplication issue

The `playbooks/plugins/lookups/py_pkgs.py` had an issue where it's
assumed that the name of a package is always split on an "_" however
a repo name could be anything before the `_git_repo` portion. This
commit corrects that issue.

Change-Id: I49f8a7726ed99e47ff514cdf6e61472fac5b9ed4
Partially-Implements: blueprint master-kilofication
(cherry picked from commit 2198cb665f2b47b79c4283f85ea65d501a2177da)

commit_message:
Add option to enable/disable the nova v2.1 API

In the kilo release the nova v2.1 API is tied to the v3 API, so v3 needs
to be enabled for v2.1 to be enabled as well. This change adds a setting
to control whether the v2.1 API should be enabled or disabled. If v2.1
is enabled then v3 will be enabled as well, but without registering it
with the keystone catalog.

Change-Id: I1e80189bbcbef1dd712cd6a527b5b59aa939e9e1
Closes-Bug: #1445524

This is pretty much what we talked about previously. The big downside i can see is that at least one request is going to get skewed because the first auth request will happen within the time scope of the first call. 

A better way that i see is that the return from request is a requests.Response. A requests.Response has a .history list with all the redirects and stuff, each of which is also a Response.

Each requests.Response also contains an .elapsed property which is how long the request took. A timing session (subclass is good) should simply save a copy of every response that is returned from request() and then if print timings are on you can interate through all those responses and their histories and print the URL that was called and the time that was taken.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2015-03-13 14:46:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Fix session timing

Subclass keystoneclient.session.Session to add the timing hooks to
record the elapsed time returned by requests.Response objects, including
the redirection history.  Redirects are included individually and not
rolled into the total time for the original request.

This works for all clients that use OSC's session.

Closes-Bug: #1402577
Change-Id: I9360c90c151579b89a37edb8c11c17feb15b3cb9

commit_message:
Fix test_add_list_remove_router_on_l3_agent race for dvr

This patch fixes a race-condition raised by the
test_add_list_remove_router_on_l3_agent for DVR routers.

Sometimes this test fails because when a port is added
to a router, the dhcp port for that particular subnet
is not created on time and so when the router tries to
bind to an agent, it throws an error since there are
no valid serviceable DVR ports on that subnet.

This patch will wait until a dhcp port is created on
that subnet and then associate the subnet with a router.

Closes-Bug: #1442494

Change-Id: I77393abddd7eefee4604f2a867f41880e4bc14d0

commit_message:
Only use operational LIFs for iscsi target details

When Nova invokes our cDOT driver's initialize_connection() method
in order to attach an iSCSI volume to an instance, we have been
returning the first target from the list of targets returned from
the filer API call to get iscsi target details.  In failover mode,
this may be a target with a LIF that is down, causing the attach
attempt to fail in Nova.

This commit fixes that issue so that attaches still work in
failover by returning the first target with an *operational* LIF.

Code here is a literal copy of code merged into Kilo but because
our Cinder drivers were reorganized and refactored in Kilo the
code appears in different files.

Closes-bug: 1437419

Change-Id: I3f53c3644f7d94f5188151c16d70e565b745ad4a
(cherry picked from commit 9d77c0e1435d377790eaf812691b29e8b7a6b2c7)

commit_message:
ensure that grenade db is fresh on each run

The grenade db is really just an ini file, but there is no reason why
it should persist in a second run of grenade, and it actually causes
issues if it does. Blank it out in the init phase to ensure we're
starting with a blank store.

Change-Id: I22a2b53739153011f5c250739278719259ad7860

commit_message:
Add workaround to work with cirros image

The cirros image uses an old dhcp client which does not work
properly with hardware that has checksum offload enabled.  Add
a bootp rule to rewrite the checksum via iptables.

Latest cirros 0.3.33 is afflicted by this bug.

Change-Id: Ibfd1f87af5d0bef9fcb1354121e76e4e0db8ab5e

commit_message:
Add option to enable/disable the nova v2.1 API

In the kilo release the nova v2.1 API is tied to the v3 API, so v3 needs
to be enabled for v2.1 to be enabled as well. This change adds a setting
to control whether the v2.1 API should be enabled or disabled. If v2.1
is enabled then v3 will be enabled as well, but without registering it
with the keystone catalog.

Change-Id: I1e80189bbcbef1dd712cd6a527b5b59aa939e9e1
Closes-Bug: #1445524
(cherry picked from commit fcc4144692f3d8310481a77e54e6ef7c2614b57c)

The new style oslo-config-generator needs an entry point and
we have exposed this in other modules

Closes-Bug: #1424576

commit_message:
todo: note neutronclient binding:profile patch

Add a reference to the python-neutronclient patch needed for sending a
custom binding:profile.

In passing, remove completed devstack task and update the description
of another task to not dictate the solution, because the solution is
likely to be just to install it from pypi once we get it posted there.

Change-Id: I4d2f6c444f2ff4156d01d0a91fee92b8a51e887b

commit_message:
Neutron doa in current form

The nova-config.sh script was exiting because of incorrect shell syntax.

The correct syntax for a regex search is
[[ haystack =~ needle ]].  The .*needle.* is unnecessary.  I think this shell
script exited because a period was missing.

Change-Id: I3aca5e0729eb5fedbe9ecb4d75ed85d5a1c7815a

commit_message:
Move cliff gerrit announcements to the sdk channel

The SDK team has taken over managing cliff, so move announcements of
changes and merges out of the Oslo channel and into the SDK team
channel.

Change-Id: Ie31e82fa8d24b9bb2539913feb3be1410db3c301

commit_message:
Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

Remove the modules and tests that have moved to oslo.log. Replace the
use of oslo.log with the standard library logging module.

Replace calls to LOG.deprecated() with a new function in versionutils
that is copied from the body of the old implementation.

Add fatal_deprecations configuration option to versionutils, where it is
used now instead of the old log module.

Change-Id: I5903f9a9c521789cbf3381d9741a8a5308767e2d
Closes-Bug: #1373120
Blueprint: fix-import-cycle-log-and-versionutils

commit_message:
Remove code that moved to oslo.i18n

Remove the modules that went to oslo.i18n and their tests, then update
the other modules and tests to use oslo.i18n.

There are a few cases where other modules that will be deleted from the
incubator for juno had references to gettextutils, especially for their
tests. These are commented out as an expedient way to make the tests
run, in anticipation of the files being removed separately.

Change-Id: Ib80a3f0b0f6e96065e86a9b477aebd8bce1201ba
Closes-Bug: #1371702

commit_message:
Enhance versionutils.deprecated to work with classes

If object being decorated is a function, it is processed as before,
otherwise a new class is created which logs deprecated message when
class is instantiated. This change comes with 2 unit tests.

Closes-Bug: #1337889
Change-Id: Ib5cc04bea0ff2ea588618599f4e42df16cb85a0d

commit_message:
VPNaaS Remove dependency on Neutron for unit test

Instead of mocking the execute() method from Neutron, we'll mock
higher up, at _execute() for the *Swan process. This will isolate
the tests from Neutron.

Found that some DVR tests were not activated (missing BaseTestCase
inheritance), and cleaned up a few tests.

Change-Id: Ia7655714088f53478d4286b8f61fca77688c1ecc
Closes-Bug: #1438259

commit_message:
Add a spec for basic high availability

This basic design replicates the entire congress server and uses the database
for shared state.

commit_message:
Update gerritbot #openstack-infra from governance

Add all missing Infra projects (except planet, changes there are
fairly uninteresting for us) per the openstack/governance
projects.yaml list, and remove the nonexistent gerrit-trigger-plugin
repo too. Also add stable branches for openstack/requirements since
that's been frequently requested.

Change-Id: Ie1bfc17c0822b23eeb155c14ec3ccabac4e07e45

commit_message:
Fixes unit-test in troveclient

1. Renames tes___eq__ to be test___eq__,
   because earlier method was not being called.
2. Corrects the test-code in test___eq__,
   for the failures it gave when it started running.
3. Removes some unused code from tests,
   there were few lines/methods which were not used by tests
   just removed/updated them.

Change-Id: I90aa8cb9bb9f5d15697f00df0ba1defa0ef7be59
Closes-Bug: #1441518

Allow deprecated decorator to specify no plan for removal

Allow the @deprecated decorator to specify functionality as deprecated
but not slate any release for removal of the deprecated functionality.

This makes it so that use-ephemeral isn't a hard coded requirement
rather it is just a default for DIB_COMMON_ELEMENTS.

This previous assertion (that use-ephemeral is required) is

commit_message:
Don't hard code the use-ephemeral element

This makes it so that use-ephemeral isn't a hard coded requirement
rather it is just a default for DIB_COMMON_ELEMENTS.

This previous assertion (that use-ephemeral is required) is
no longer true with some TripleO configuration tools (like puppet).
When using Puppet use-ephemeral doesn't hurt anything but it
shouldn't be required... and could be confusing to some users.

Change-Id: I9bd11ce934deb5fd33b9a9c08f741aac216be8c8

commit_message:
Add more detail to method not supported exception

Add more detail to method not supported exception including
module and class name.  Previously, the exception would just
give the method name which wasn't very useful.

Change-Id: I838fb31bd5177f58df4a384796551747bbcfaa5d

commit_message:
Add module name to repr string

Add the module name to the repr string so we can better identify
the resource that created the string.  This is also convenient
for recreating the object from a string such as:

    python examples/get.py openstack/compute/v2/server.py --data "openstack.compute.v2.server.Server(attrs={u'id': u'85d8ecf3-3757-43fd-b7a2-eb6636f7af1c', u'name': u'jenkins'}, loaded=True)"

Change-Id: I7a8bdabd8150e0bd06ec46deecf81eaa126907ab

commit_message:
Create config file in merge_config_file

Change If132a94e53545d9134859aa508da7b9819ede2f8 introduced a small
regression; it added an "inidelete" which looks in the config file to
delete rows.

However, at least for the test-case, the config file isn't created
yet.  The end result is that the test fails but we don't notice.

 2015-04-17 00:55:03.169 | merge_config_file test-multiline: sed: can't read test-multiline.conf: No such file or directory
 2015-04-17 00:55:03.195 | OK

So fix this up by creating the config-file if it isn't there.

Also, add "-e" to the test file so we catch things like this in the
future.

Change-Id: I43a4ecc247f19cccf51d5931dfb687adbd23d6b1

commit_message:
Fix die_if_not_set tests

The "die_if_not_set" test has the LINENO as a positional argument.
The existing tests are not passing this in, so they are failing.

Along with this, remove the "-x" from the invocation and hide the
output of the tests that are expected to fail to avoid confusion.

Change-Id: Ibf6b9d7bb72b9f92831e1a90292ff8b0bec7faea

The existing test_functions.sh is really testing true/false.  Move
that to test_truefalse.sh

Then move functions.sh to test_functions.sh.  This will ensure it is
run during unit testing from run-tests.sh

Change-Id: I959ac38c946da1fb47458b8c4f09157f74f0e644
'}]
commit_message:
Move function.sh to test_functions.sh

run_tests.sh runs tests starting with test_*

The existing test_functions.sh is really testing true/false.  Move
that to test_truefalse.sh

Then move functions.sh to test_functions.sh.  This will ensure it is
run during unit testing from run-tests.sh

Change-Id: I959ac38c946da1fb47458b8c4f09157f74f0e644

commit_message:
Fix return of test_ini_config & test_meta_config

Convert test_ini_config to use the "passed / failed" functions in
unittest.sh.  test_meta_config wraps everything into a function; it's
not work unrolling this so just make sure it exits with non-zero if a
test fails.

Change-Id: I9e9883fdad42358255383eede9121b1d361799c8

helper.  Also keep a count of passed and failed tests.  Later changes

commit_message:
Add "passed" and "failed" functions

Add two generic "passed" and "failed" functions to the unittest
helper.  Also keep a count of passed and failed tests.  Later changes
will use these functions to ensure they exit with a correct return
code.

Change-Id: I8574dcb1447b04fcda3d72df0bf8605cf7488d3c

commit_message:
More docstring cleanups/tweaks

Ensure jsonutils and msgpackutils headers are linkable and
connect into there associated functions and classes so that
clicking on links works (instead of not working).

Change-Id: Ifa28421e7d21a85290ee13d04918325c3f991b92

commit_message:
Add docstring(s) to handler registry(s)

Ensure that the handler registry (and the default
registry) appears in the generated docs and make sure that a
note is added that we can not currently serialize and restore
tuples correctly (at least until the mentioned pull request is
merged and a release is made avaiable with it).

Change-Id: Ic5b9c41b401c6983bd416fd6726319cc674c1759

commit_message:
Add aggregate metrics to libvirt

This patch adds extra metrics to the libvirt plugin, gathering aggregate
data across all hosted instances.  These include:
- nova.vm.mem.total_allocated_mb
- nova.vm.cpu.total_allocated
- nova.vm.disk.total_allocated_gb

Change-Id: Iaa166784047273eec10d0835d81750116fb0f64d

Revert "Separate api and registry packages for Red Hat"

Due to a patch in RDO packaging, puppet-glance is broken for RHEL platforms.

This reverts commit 5f15e05704b2e549b8fab1c643a6ee743a0e92f4.

commit_message:
Allow policy-name in head of rules with modal

For rules that have modals in the head, it makes sense to
allow the head to reference another policy.  Examples:

execute[neutron:disconnectNetwork(x,y)] :- ...
insert[nova:server(x,y,z)] :- ...

Policy is still prohibited in the head of rules without
modals since the meaning of such rules is still ambiguous.

Change-Id: Ifffa813f5c569002a48b3164f6c33ec469a92ca3

commit_message:
Consolidate the APIs for getting consoles

We have different public API for getting console access for each kind of
console that is supported in Nova. The proposal is to consolidate all
these APIs into one.

Previously-approved: kilo

APIImpact

blueprint consolidate-console-api

Change-Id: I14daca240d5a7b41c1ce75a0240dce3421845128

commit_message:
New VIF type to allow routing VM data instead of bridging it

We propose to add a new VIF type, VIF_TYPE_TAP, whose meaning is that
the host side of a VNIC to a VM is - at least initially - a simple TAP
interface that is not plugged into a bridge or vSwitch.  A Neutron
agent can continue the process of deciding how to handle data from
that interface, and how to deliver data to it - but this is beyond the
scope of the initial TAP interface setup that Nova needs to provide.

Previously-approved: kilo
Change-Id: I3c5371b865eadc458ce25ba85953d1ddecab2506

commit_message:
Refactor some service tests and make them not require db

This refactors service tests in a few different ways:

 - Remove unnecessary calls
 - Make tests test what they say instead of something that other tests
   already cover (make TestLauncher into something else than testing
   what test_service_random_port already does)
 - Make them not require db

Change-Id: Ic2dfbc0d2ccf7a1f71929b78d7c7d784a2f8b7f5

Remove and deprecate unused conductor service calls

A previous change converted service and servicegroup to objects.
This change removes the now unused service methods from conductor.

[{'created': '2015-04-15 23:52:58.000000000', 'message': 'Fix retries in grab_console_log.sh

We implemented retries of console log grabbing to workaround occasional
jenkins 502 errors, but this is running under set -e so curl returning a
non zero error message resulted in short circuiting the retries and
failed the jobs.

Fix this with a simple || true appendage to the curl command so that any
failed curls can error properly without affecting the error checking in
the script. We will then retry until we eventually give up.

Change-Id: I0a784aa45bff7de5b411372ccecc569ec148ecc5
'}]
commit_message:
Fix retries in grab_console_log.sh

We implemented retries of console log grabbing to workaround occasional
jenkins 502 errors, but this is running under set -e so curl returning a
non zero error message resulted in short circuiting the retries and
failed the jobs.

Fix this with a simple || true appendage to the curl command so that any
failed curls can error properly without affecting the error checking in
the script. We will then retry until we eventually give up.

Change-Id: I0a784aa45bff7de5b411372ccecc569ec148ecc5

commit_message:
Capture dhcp during multinode n-net runs

Nova net connected cirros VMs occasionally have dhcp discovery fail.
Capture dhcp across the flat network to try and diagnose why.

Change-Id: I2e2305b0a430ecf20d08c0ed3668ca9c6632309f

commit_message:
Add support for nvme devices to pmanager

nvme devices show up as e.g. nvme0n1p3. _pseparator needs
to return a 'p' separator for these devices.

Change-Id: Id2ebcaa5b1332c0e00c54440ee19e6c0cb859e00
Closes-bug: #1372547

commit_message:
TripleO: Add f20puppet-ha check job

This commit aims to enable a new check job (non-voting) at the moment
to validate a deployment of the overcloud using puppet in an HA setup.

In the code it remplaces the 'precise-ha' job because this job is not
maintained any more.

Change-Id: I74e41db02cd580a2f61db042acb6296a996e57e1

commit_message:
Convert service and servicegroup to objects

This converts service and servicegroup to use objects instead of
proxying through conductor.

Adds missing object registration to cert and console scripts.

Related to blueprint liberty-objects

Change-Id: I87b077699c2ecbc25a83e5844e8c69fe147cec01

commit_message:
Remove unused policy rule for get_trust

The policy rule for get_trust is misleading for operators
since it is not used by the trust controller.

Change-Id: I885ccbafef8bb9ca73ca6fab110176291bb3a542
Closes-Bug: #1444748

commit_message:
Fixing n-crt removal from stackrc

The commit 279cfe75198c723519f1fb361b2bff3c641c6cef removed the n-crt
service from the default devstack setup. As such, the stack.sh script
begun to thrown the following error when trying to "nova x509-create-cert":

  ERROR (ClientException): The server has either erred or is incapable of
  performing the requested operation. (HTTP 500)

This patches reintroduces the n-crt as a default service.

Change-Id: Id9695a37e1c6df567f2c86baa4475225adcfb0ee
Closes-bug: #1441007

commit_message:
[Launch Instance Fix] Security Group Nova Net

When nova networking is enabled, the input to security
groups needs to be by name.  When neutron, it needs
to be by id. This solves that issues.

Change-Id: If32671af90facd16e60caa33ed84ba7c9796ad11
Closes-Bug: #1445235

[{'created': '2015-03-07 03:08:09.000000000', 'message': 'Fix LUN misalignment issue with NetApp iSCSI drivers

This patch fixes LUN misalignment issues that can be
experienced when provisioning Cinder volumes with the iSCSI
protocol. In the fix, two new SAN options for configuring
LUN OS and initiator OS used while attaching volume can be
specified. This gives the admin flexibility to configure
backends correctly for multiple hypervisor and guest OS
platforms.

Closes-Bug: 1410107

commit_message:
Fix LUN misalignment issue with NetApp iSCSI drivers

This patch fixes LUN misalignment issues that can be
experienced when provisioning Cinder volumes with the iSCSI
protocol. In the fix, two new SAN options for configuring
LUN OS and initiator OS used while attaching volume can be
specified. This gives the admin flexibility to configure
backends correctly for multiple hypervisor and guest OS
platforms.

Closes-Bug: 1410107

Change-Id: If09e1ad41880e8070afddde5606c6536b03396fe

commit_message:
Remove keystone public/admin_endpoint options

The public_endpoint and admin_endpoint options are used to set the base
hostname when listing versions. If they are not provided then the
response will use the same hostname as the request was made with - which
is almost always what you actually want.

This means devstack will respond correctly to a version list when behind
a floating IP for example.

Change-Id: Idc48b9d7bee9751deb24d730fdc560b163f39dfe

commit_message:
Remove assigned protocol before removing IdP

We should rely less on specific RDBMS to keep referential integrity,
thus, the assigned protocols of IdP should be removed explicitly before
remove IdP itself.

bp ondelete-cascade

Change-Id: If59728b0ca711cd8f28695c85ff1db864c572d96

commit_message:
Remove direct DB usage from NetApp driver

Update setup_server() method in driver. This driver should
return backend details instead of direct DB API call.

Change-Id: I4dc33695d377765a6139b646d0398b279aa31a8b
Closes-Bug: #1444871

commit_message:
Move rabbit/kombu settings to oslo_messaging_rabbit section

Kilo oslo-messaging deprecates rabbit/kombu settings in the
DEFAULT section.

Move these settings to proper oslo_messaging_rabbit section.

Change-Id: Ica8cd70ece41f55b827f74d3f14cbc35f37ae13d

commit_message:
Add volume status check to api detach method

Should be checking the status of the volume before
firing off the detach call.  This change will result
in the same behavior/exception being raised if you call
detach on a volume that's not attached, but it does it
sooner rather than later rather than going through the
rpc chain down to the manager.

Change-Id: I25c074ec233c6990514fe28661181a38224756cd
Closes-Bug: #1445247

commit_message:
Propose removal of eventlet from web server command

The use of eventlet in the Werkzeug server is redundant and can lead
to confusion. The spec proposes getting rid of it and only using
eventlet on the other command line scripts.

Change-Id: I140f3a329d840046fd2db1c2ce1235fc7666c80e

commit_message:
Ensure ratio calculated for Ceph journals is an integer

When creating journal paritions an osd-to-journal ratio is
calculated. This ratio is later used to determine the size
of each individual journal partition. The ratio was a floating
point number which would result in floating point partition
sizes causing dd commands to fail.

Change-Id: Ide1311de3dd3c4a859b5d9b00f3e86912489d761
Closes-bug: #1444459

errors with proper error messages to provide users with more

The safe_quote() method is used for ensuring the tokens that we send as a URL
are URL-safe. This doens't need to be done on the V3 side since we are using
HTTP Headers to transfer the token_id. Using the safe_quote method on Fernet
tokens can alter their appearance and cause them to fail when validating them
online against the Keystone server.

Change-Id: I0bc7459af897ac03920a6268c3467b19f826e634
Closes-Bug: 1433372
"}]
commit_message:
Don't safe_quote for V3 in auth_token.

The safe_quote() method is used for ensuring the tokens that we send as a URL
are URL-safe. This doens't need to be done on the V3 side since we are using
HTTP Headers to transfer the token_id. Using the safe_quote method on Fernet
tokens can alter their appearance and cause them to fail when validating them
online against the Keystone server.

Change-Id: I0bc7459af897ac03920a6268c3467b19f826e634
Closes-Bug: 1433372

As far as building of OS images is nothing more than
just a stage of the whole OS installing procedure
it is sounds rational to implement this in terms
of fuel-agent. Besides, we already have plenty of utilities
which could be useful during building of images.
And some tasks are the same like pre-configuring
some files inside target OS.

Related-bug: #1433193
Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images

commit_message:
IBP: Added driver and objects for building images

As far as building of OS images is nothing more than
just a stage of the whole OS installing procedure
it is sounds rational to implement this in terms
of fuel-agent. Besides, we already have plenty of utilities
which could be useful during building of images.
And some tasks are the same like pre-configuring
some files inside target OS.

commit_message:
Branch update utility

This script was created to rapidly interate through a repo_package file
that contains git sources and set the various repositories inside to
the head of given branch via the SHA. This makes it possible to update
all of the services that we support in an "automated" fashion.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication

Change-Id: Ied01e4968ad7b1b4bd6ecde902bab9e963417358
(cherry picked from commit e4a032b12f9540fd650196195df0e50c8f9fe4dc)

[{'created': '2015-04-16 10:51:38.000000000', 'message': 'IBP: Changed image metadata format

New metadata format consists of tree parts
1) images metadata (md5 sums, sizes, filenames, formats)
2) repos metadata (which repos were used
to build this set of images)
3) packages metadata (just a list of packages
installed into an image)

The motivation behind is to split the image abstraction
(which is not always just OS image) from repos and packages
abstractions.

Change-Id: I5ce3e291a3ad7a1b7012b5c504ecdc97dd4023e2
Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images
Related-bug: #1433193
'}]
commit_message:
IBP: Changed image metadata format

New metadata format consists of tree parts
1) images metadata (md5 sums, sizes, filenames, formats)
2) repos metadata (which repos were used
to build this set of images)
3) packages metadata (just a list of packages
installed into an image)

The motivation behind is to split the image abstraction
(which is not always just OS image) from repos and packages
abstractions.

Change-Id: I5ce3e291a3ad7a1b7012b5c504ecdc97dd4023e2
Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images
Related-bug: #1433193

commit_message:
IBP: install fuel-agent into mcollective docker

We implemented target OS image building
in terms of fuel-agent. So, we need this package
to be installed into mcollective docker container.
fuel-agent provides build_image executable entry
point.

Change-Id: Ic7d10fead8423cdb8fd33c3244e0670d4ed19f4f
Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images
Related-bug: #1433193

commit_message:
ironic/tests/drivers/ilo: Add spec= & autospec=True to mocks

Add spec= and autospec=True to mocks

Fixed issues with misspelled mock asserts discovered because of this
work.

Example errors
    assert_called_ince_with()
    called_once_with()

Change-Id: Ie883399427e8e1066da1e166e3a8dbf546e57bee

commit_message:
Added support of sahara with tls-proxy service

Now devstack will configure tls-proxy for sahara as well as for
other openstack services.

Change-Id: I7b0f2f0773cd3619a33cac66d40f3d0ce0f5432c
Closes-Bug: #1419163

commit_message:
Switching Sahara to https in case of USE_SSL=True

Sahara will work over https in case if USE_SSL is set.

Note, this patch requires https://review.openstack.org/#/c/145383/
which is not merged yet.

Change-Id: I9e0069cfe72323a069a4205ca2f882c7a3ad17e0
Closes-Bug: #1419162

i'd just like to confirm we don't have some other bug before we land this... I'm guessing this started breaking when the service reduction change went in.

 [iwienand@fedora19 devstack]$ git grep libxml2
 files/debs/ceilometer-collector:libxml2-dev
 files/debs/devlibs:libxml2-dev  # lxml
 files/debs/glance:libxml2-dev
 files/debs/nova:python-libxml2

so nova should have brought in python-libxml2, which should be 2.9.1 on a trusty host which is greater than what you need there

 Downloading/unpacking lxml>=2.3 (from -r /opt/stack/tempest/requirements.txt (line 7))

is nova not installed on this host?  

[1] http://packages.ubuntu.com/trusty/python-libxml2"}, {'account_id': 15866, 'date': '2015-04-08 06:15:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

The OP of the Bug (https://bugs.launchpad.net/devstack/+bug/1225395) was installing devstack on Ubuntu 12.04.
However, I see that in multi-node setup there might be a use case when there is only keystone/ceilometer on the node'}, {'account_id': 15866, 'date': '2015-04-08 06:16:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Another proposal is that we remove it from the individual projects ad add these 2 in files/debs/general since quite a number of projects seem to need these.'}, {'account_id': 7118, 'date': '2015-04-08 07:08:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

so it's libxslt that's actually missing.  it is still not clear from the partial log how things ended up like this [1].

the long term intent is I guess to build this as a wheel and use that.  

in the mean time, might as well do it like this -- as long as nova is including the packaged version that's going to override most everything in a single-node version anyway; i.e. installing the dev packages is just wasted time and space in that case so they don't need to be in "general"

[1] https://launchpadlibrarian.net/150255293/log'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2015-04-17 13:17:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-17 13:17:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

commit_message:
Added libxml2-dev package as a pre-requisite when installing tempest.
This is required so that devstack can be installed on vanilla Ubuntu systems.

Closes-Bug: 1225395

Change-Id: Id9116e00e18c23e8e6391d8aa652c04d8bdb86c3

the Neutron L3 agent is modified to support
dual-stack.

merged.

With the implementation of dual-stack gateway support
as part of the Neutron multiple-ipv6-prefixes
blueprint, some of the code in the IPv6 setup in the
DevStack neutron script can be removed. This code
had been added temporarily, with a TODO note
indicating that this code should be removed when
the Neutron L3 agent is modified to support
dual-stack.

This change also includes a modification of the
default prefix to be used for the public IPv6
subnet. The new value (2001:df8::/64) is a special
reserved prefix that will be treated as non-routable
external to the OpenStack instance.

This change should not be merged until after
the changes for:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/161085/
(and changes that this depends upon) have been
merged.

'}, {'created': '2015-04-02 13:41:20.000000000', 'message': "Remove unused IPv6 setup from DevStack neutron script

With the implementation of dual-stack gateway support
as part of the Neutron multiple-ipv6-prefixes
blueprint, some of the code in the IPv6 setup in the
DevStack neutron legacy script must be removed. This
code had been added temporarily, with a TODO note
indicating that this code should be removed when
the Neutron L3 agent is modified to support
dual-stack.

Without this change, DevStack will fail to configure
the Neutron router gateway interface (there will be
no external connectivity) whenever IP_VERSION is set
to either '6' or '4+6' in localrc/local.conf, since
first DevStack and later the Neutron L3 agent will be
trying to ADD the IPv6 address to the router gateway
interface.

This change also includes a modification of the
default prefix to be used for the public IPv6
subnet. The new value (2001:df8::/64) is a special
reserved prefix that will be treated as non-routable
external to the OpenStack instance.

Change-Id: I85fe68782bc54f28f3e14aa4a1d042cb15959dac
Partially-implements: blueprint multiple-ipv6-prefixes

DevStack neutron legacy script must be removed. This
code had been added temporarily, with a TODO note
indicating that this code should be removed when

Without this change, DevStack will fail to configure

no external connectivity) whenever IP_VERSION is set
to '4+6' in localrc/local.conf, since

commit_message:
Remove unused IPv6 setup from DevStack neutron script

With the implementation of dual-stack gateway support
as part of the Neutron multiple-ipv6-prefixes
blueprint, some of the code in the IPv6 setup in the
DevStack neutron legacy script must be removed. This
code had been added temporarily, with a TODO note
indicating that this code should be removed when
the Neutron L3 agent is modified to support
dual-stack.

Without this change, DevStack will fail to configure
the Neutron router gateway interface (there will be
no external connectivity) whenever IP_VERSION is set
to '4+6' in localrc/local.conf, since
first DevStack and later the Neutron L3 agent will be
trying to ADD the IPv6 address to the router gateway
interface.

This change also includes a modification of the
default prefix to be used for the public IPv6
subnet. The new value (2001:df8::/64) is a special
reserved prefix that will be treated as non-routable
external to the OpenStack instance.

Change-Id: I85fe68782bc54f28f3e14aa4a1d042cb15959dac
Partially-implements: blueprint multiple-ipv6-prefixes

commit_message:
Use entry_points for manila scripts

Manila scripts located in bin/* should be covered with unit tests.
In order to add unit tests for bin/* scripts:
- all
- api
- manage
- scheduler
- share
we move them into manila/cmd and use pbr to setup console scripts
which will call the respective main function of each script under manila/cmd.
It will allow us to import from manila.cmd and individually test each 'main' function.

Add unit tests for manila/cmd/* scripts.

Implements bp unit-tests-for-manila-scripts

Change-Id: I9be6b948a6de7ba76405411e98d7531cf225b57e

I have couple of questions.

1)Errors & warnings identified in 'gate-puppet-neutron-puppet-lint': Is there a way to run this locally on my machine. I ran 'puppet-lint' on my Ubuntu machine and the Warnings showed up are different from that of 'gate-puppet-neutron-puppet-lint'.

2) In my next run (103466) I fixed all the errors barring very few warnings. But still I see the below Failure message. I could not figure out the real reason.

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: quoted boolean value found on line 52
2014-06-30 06:15:12.886 | manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: quoted boolean value found on line 67

2014-06-30 06:15:12.887 | manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: double quoted string containing no variables on line 69
2014-06-30 06:15:12.887 | manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: string containing only a variable on line 76
2014-06-30 06:15:13.140 | Build step 'Execute shell' marked build as failure"}, {'account_id': 6754, 'date': '2014-07-19 01:29:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hi Kiran, sorry to just be getting back to this--I've been out of the office on paternity leave following the birth of my new daughter.  Regarding those warnings:

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: quoted boolean value found on line 52 2014-06-30 06:15:12.886 

This indicates that you have a string (e.g. 'true') instead instead of a boolean (true).  That may or may not be what you intended (both are often used).

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: quoted boolean value found on line 67 2014-06-30 06:15:12.886 

Likewise.

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: quoted boolean value found on line 69 2014-06-30 06:15:12.886 

Likewise.

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: quoted boolean value found on line 165 2014-06-30 06:15:12.886 

Likewise.

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: double quoted string containing no variables on line 67 2014-06-30 06:15:12.887 

If you aren't interpolating any variables in a string, use single quotes instead of double quotes.  Refer to the style guide here:

http://docs.puppetlabs.com/guides/style_guide.html#quoting

| manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: double quoted string containing no variables on line 69 2014-06-30 06:15:12.887 

Likewise.

manifests/agents/n1kv_vem.pp - WARNING: string containing only a variable on line 76 2014-06-30 06:15:13.140

This is similar: if all you have inside of a quoted string is a variable to be interpolated, don't quote it at all.  See:

http://docs.puppetlabs.com/guides/style_guide.html#quoting

As for running puppet-lint locally, I usually just install puppet-lint via pip and use that.  I believe the gate check also installs puppet-lint via pip, but don't quote me on it...I'd have to go sort through the infra config to find out for sure.  In any case, the differences between minor versions are generally small so that should take care of the bulk of the issues before it hits the gate check."}, {'account_id': 11370, 'date': '2014-08-07 19:29:42.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-07 19:29:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

My point earlier was that those should just be parameters rather than being hashed together rather than that they shouldn't be present at all.  If they're seldom used, that's fine--just use reasonable defaults and the composition layer can simply not override them."}, {'account_id': 6754, 'date': '2014-08-15 15:04:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Mark,
Regd your comments:
1)additional_params: 'node_type' parameter was missing in my last diff. I added it now. 'vteps_in_same_subnet' is present. 'additional-params' we thought was only for some advanced parameters which will not be exposed to common user. You can treat them as some params, which will be used for Perf-Evaluation (control number of threads etc). We could take them away also later. In this context, I thought instead of making changes every time in upstream manifest files, we will use this opaque param.

2)I added UT cases you suggested (covering almost all class params). WRT, testing the 'sysctl' settings, the test was passing well in RedHat OpenStack env. But when run on my Commit machine (Ubuntu env), its causing puppet failures. To fix that I had to add couple of lines (.fixtures.yml and Modulefile)

3)'Proxy' setting for yum repo. For entire deployment the proxy will be set in 'yum.conf'. This need not be set for Cisco-Yum repo specifically, which in this context will only be holding N1KV images."}, {'account_id': 11370, 'date': '2014-08-15 21:19:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
New manifest file to deploy Cisco N1KV-VEM

Background on 'N1KV-VEM: It is the host-side component of N1KV
implementing the notion of Virtual Ports for VM Interfaces and also
handling the VM data-traffic. VEM is implemented as a couple of
user-space processes and also has a KLM for efficient data-path
switching.

VEM manifests does: setting up the Config-File for VEM service,
Starting VEM service and finally adding physical ports (along with
port-profile) to the VEM

Change-Id: Ibc8f1c4d2d743589e452ae6d1d87b5bfa123bc3a

Document nova-network single-host mode with vCenter

- Document important fact that nova-network works in single-host mode
  when vCenter is enabled and what might happen if it crashes

Change-Id: I8a78c49aaa8eb035535c911ecc9d141ba93bbf0e
Implements: blueprint vmware-dual-hypervisor

commit_message:
[install-guide] [yum] install openstack-neutron on compute nodes

The /etc/neutron/policy.json file is part of the package
openstack-neutron and has to be installed to be able to start the
neutron-openvswitch-agent service. This solves the following issue:

ConfigFilesNotFoundError: Failed to find some config files: policy.json

Partially implements bp installguide-kilo.

Change-Id: Id87b5ce70f19168491b5ee312c5647157458421c

(1 comment)

The spec needs some more information like the following:
Looking at the change for openstack-manuals, you add lots of different options on how to build the guide. It's not clear to me what all of this is about. Please explain whether you produce a single guide or multiple content from one guide. If it's the later, explain what it is."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2015-04-03 17:35:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

The idea is that we want to make it easy to create guides for all of the available SDKs for the OpenStack APIs that are in the wild. During this week we focused on writing examples for libcloud. 

Ideally, we'd publish the guide for SDKs/languages that have sufficient content, and the tox builds make it easy to do so."}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-04-03 18:11:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Sean, please add this in the spec so that it's clear.

Also, let's discuss where this should live. I suggest to publish on developer.openstack.org.

Do we want an own team working on this? In that case, let's create a specific repository for it (renaming stackforge/faas would be one option for that). Otherwise we can add it to api-site (for publishing to developer.o.o) or to openstack-manuals (for publishing on docs.o.o)."}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-04-06 17:53:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Thanks Sean for working on this spec to help us understand. I've added a lot of implementation questions to that section."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2015-04-08 14:21:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-04-08 20:36:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Adding Tom and Christian as reviewers.'}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2015-04-09 07:19:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Yup, so he content should to be published to developer.openstack.org

How would you like that to happen?

I think it's best for the app to continue live in it's own repo separate from the content."}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2015-04-10 08:15:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(2 comments)

The content created during the sprint should be separated from the app. The content created during the sprint documents how to use the OpenStack API and several OpenStack SDKs and the app is only an example use case. In theory the used app (Faafo at the moment) can be replaced in the future (or maybe we want to add a second use case) by an other app. The content should not directly depend on the app itself. If we put the content into the repository of the app we are restricted to the app itself. Also I think that the focus of the documentation placed inside the repository of the app is different from the focus of the content created during the sprint. The documentation inside the repository of the app describes how to use the app itself (how to create a development environment, example outputs, ..), not how to use OpenStack SDKs and the OpenStack API. Because the intent of the created content is to provide, maintain, and enhance an OpenStack document for OpenStack users to improve the users experience and to decrease the initial hurdle the content should live inside the openstack-manuals repository. At the moment we are using speciality teams to maintain guides like the Installation Guide or the User Guide and I think we should do the same for this document.'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2015-04-10 08:15:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

If not, we need to create a new repository.

If there are enough people for the first application that want to continue working on this, a separate repo might be better."}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2015-04-14 06:35:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

I'm waiting for a suggestion on that :) Do you have one?"}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2015-04-14 06:40:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

Data point: everyone (bar one) who worked on the guide (including the offsite testers) is an existing docs contributor.'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-04-14 06:42:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

Tom, for me it depends on (expected) team size and commitment.

With two docs core beeing part of the sprint - and an initial smallish team - I suggest to go to api-site.

If you know more people will contributing soon and thus the team is growing: Either start in api-site and split-up if needed or start directly with a separate repository.

But it's up to your team members, if all current contributors have a strong preference for either, go for it ;)"}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2015-04-14 06:44:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

Thanks for talking though it with me Andreas.

commit_message:
Getting rid of "policies" keyword

* Removed "policies" keyword
* Removed obsolete stubs for trigger specs
* Other minor renamings and refactorings
* Fixed "join" tests: all partial join tests were not thread-safe

Change-Id: I31b00d5d221b3a4bf03d1ab47622692c2b0f3013

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 170, 'name': 'Mike Perez', 'email': 'thingee@gmail.com', 'username': 'thingee'}, {'_account_id': 1207, 'name': 'Duncan Thomas', 'email': 'duncan.thomas@gmail.com', 'username': 'duncan-thomas'}, {'_account_id': 1736, 'name': 'Ivan Kolodyazhny', 'email': 'e0ne@e0ne.info', 'username': 'e0ne'}, {'_account_id': 2243, 'name': 'John Griffith', 'email': 'john.griffith8@gmail.com', 'username': 'john-griffith'}, {'_account_id': 7198, 'name': 'Jay Bryant', 'email': 'jungleboyj@electronicjungle.net', 'username': 'jsbryant'}, {'_account_id': 9003, 'name': 'Tom Barron', 'email': 'tpb@dyncloud.net', 'username': 'tbarron'}]

The -1 is just for some proof-reading type fixes.  Also there are some wording suggestions which you should feel free to take or leave.'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2014-12-22 15:16:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

This idea seems worthy of consideration to me.'}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2014-12-23 15:34:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

This seems like a great idea to me. Only concern is if it has any impactat install time. I am assuming that all the necessary package are installed before trying to populate the db. Want to raise the question though. 

Probably a question we should raise to the ml to get distribution feedback. 

+1 otherwise.'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2014-12-23 16:16:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Jay, there shouldn't be any installation impact because for now we already need to get all cinder requirements installed for 'cinder-manage db sync' call."}, {'account_id': 170, 'date': '2014-12-23 18:56:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I would like more details on which cinder-manage commands we're interested in converting. Some are obvious like backup list, volume delete, etc, but things like db sync aren't implemented in the cinder rest interface. Is there a plan to expose that as well?

In general I don't really know why we have cinder-manage duplicating commands from cinderclient. I recommend we deprecate those and recommend users to use cinderclient instead."}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2014-12-23 20:36:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Ivan, thanks for the response.  I thought that was the case.

Mike, good questions.  Should see answers to those and also deprecating duplicated commends would be good.'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2014-12-23 20:50:14.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Mike, thanks for feedback.
I would like to propose to extend Cinder API. I'll update the spec and add new API methods to it"}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-01-14 19:48:49.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-01-14 20:10:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-cinder-specs-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/59/143459/4/check/gate-cinder-specs-docs/f333426//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 1m 51s
- gate-cinder-specs-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/59/143459/4/check/gate-cinder-specs-python27/3f36055/ : SUCCESS in 1m 28s'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2015-01-14 20:19:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

This has actually been a debatable topic for a while now that everybody sort of lost interest in.  Having a manage command with direct access to the DB is pretty handy for things like error recovery etc.  It's been proposed in the past to take the DB access away and run through the API, BUT there are cases where the API may not be responding/running or just something that an ADMIN needs true management capability.

If we did move this to API instead of direct access then the next debate of "why even have cinder-manage" comes back.  There's no good reason for it any more after that as everything could/should be done from client/API.'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2015-01-14 20:25:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(4 comments)

Some notes inline in addition to my comment above.  Also how would you propose setup, things like "cinder-manage db sync" work?'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-01-14 20:51:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

(3 comments)

John, thank you for such detailed response.

From the administrator point of view, i'm agree with you that it could very useful to have direct db access when API is down. But from developer side, I don't want to support two implementation of a few features even them are stable enough.
Some documented api calls inside of 'cinder-manage shell' for direct DB call could help cloud operators in an emergency but is hard enough to not use it day-by-day.

If we change cinder-manage to use client/api such things like db sync will change a deployment flow to something like: 
- create database
- run cinder-api (it could starts w/o db access)
- run sync command"}, {'account_id': 170, 'date': '2015-02-10 06:21:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I agree with John that having the ability to do this while the API is not available makes the most sense. However, I don't think it's useful then, because the administrator likely doesn't care to list volumes/backups directly from the database when their cinder api service is down. ;) I guess I don't see the usefulness of this now."}, {'account_id': 1207, 'date': '2015-04-17 12:34:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-2

(2 comments)

Some minor comments inline.

I'm very strongly against any reduction in cinder-manage, indeed I would like to add some of the old functionality back in.

During a system meltdown, the ability to bypass the API is vital - e.g. after a massive network failure, being able to verify the status of cinder while keystone is still down. I've had to do this, at 4am.

Wanting to ensure everything that can be done via cinder-manage can also be done via the REST apis is a valid aim, however that should be done by filing bugs/blueprints to add the missing interfaces, if any, not by removing cinder-manage."}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-04-17 14:37:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

John, Duncan, thanks for details review. Looks like this feature is not needed for cinder'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-04-17 14:37:30.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
cinder-manage should use API instead of direct DB communication

cinder-manage should use REST API instead of direct db calls. It will provide
more flexible way to manage Cinder via CLI and API not only for admin users
but also for Horizon and Heat users with admin permissions.

Change-Id: Id8178031d245a5ddbdf9dfc1002ec40de4bcaac2
Related-Blueprint: cinder-manage-api-usage

commit_message:
Fuel Client depends on 0.7 < pbr < 1.0

The RPM spec broken because the != 0.7 is specified
in the wrong way. This patch bumbs the minimum version
to resolve the problem.

commit_message:
Fixes the rollback of flavor resize for couchdb, db2 & vertica

- Rollback path of flavor resizing calls reset_configuration
  which was not implemented in the new datastores.
- Added a dummy implementation of reset_configuration to
  support rollback path of flavor resize.
- Also added the verifying unit-tests for reset_configuration.
- The test apart from testing the method also would help to
  improve the block coverage.

Change-Id: Iae152f8e5b4a67e2afc5ea9524014cdf0f461354
Closes-Bug: #1441574

commit_message:
Adding Bandit gate test scaffolding

Initial bits n bobs to get a working Bandit test env for tox, we
can tweek this going forward to tune our test Bandit tests etc

This is not run as part of the normal tox command, run it with
tox -e bandit

Change-Id: I257b0ac335929ad09c43f5753feaab10c269d232

commit_message:
Quota model: use HasTenantId mixin

This change simply changes the Quota model class to obtain
the tenant_id from the mixin class. As the attribute in the
mixin is identical to that in the model there is no need for
a migration.

This patch also removes a reference to quota classes in the
docstring, as Neutron does not implement those. It is good
to be careful when copying and paste code.

Change-Id: Idab15d5ef2ddd2b830a7dcde46990506064535f7
Closes-Bug: #1445169

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-25 14:36:27.000000000', 'message': "IBP: Improved data parsing flow

It is better when manager does not need to
care about calling data driver parse method but
instead manager just instantiates data driver
with raw data and then asks data driver for
ready to use objects.

Even more, it is necessary to encapsulate this logic
into a data driver itself because which schemes we
actually need (PartitionScheme, ConfigdriveScheme)
depend on the manager's do_* method we use. Some
do_* methods don't even need PartitionScheme or
ConfigdriveScheme and a user who calls for example
do_reboot method does not assume she needs to
provide fuel-agent with partitioning data.

Related-bug: #1433193
Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images
Change-Id: I79b73d63c1ecb1dd0af24bb446003cb6585d206f

commit_message:
IBP: Improved data parsing flow

It is better when manager does not need to
care about calling data driver parse method but
instead manager just instantiates data driver
with raw data and then asks data driver for
ready to use objects.

Even more, it is necessary to encapsulate this logic
into a data driver itself because which schemes we
actually need (PartitionScheme, ConfigdriveScheme)
depend on the manager's do_* method we use. Some
do_* methods don't even need PartitionScheme or
ConfigdriveScheme and a user who calls for example
do_reboot method does not assume she needs to
provide fuel-agent with partitioning data.

Related-bug: #1433193
Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images
Change-Id: I79b73d63c1ecb1dd0af24bb446003cb6585d206f

[IBP] Add build_utils

target image.

commit_message:
add back n-cert

nova-cert service is actually used by various commands during devstack
startup to get root certificates outside of the use by the ec2 api. It
should remain on as a default service.

Change-Id: I46c66ab4c2dedcb9ca1cd3e767736f215bc93869

commit_message:
Add OSSN-0047

This adds a new security note about Keystone's OS-FEDERATION

commit_message:
Enable dashboard scenario test

This commit adds the dashboard scenario test to
templates/openstack_tempest_gate.sh.j2 and fixes
tempest_dashboard_login_url and tempest_dashboard_url
since horizon is always configured to use SSL.

The dashboard scenario test involves:

* checking that login page is available
* ability to log in as a regular user
* checking that the home page loads without error

This is a rather simplistic set of tests but will provide valuable
feedback in the gate that we have not introduced any significant
dashboard regressions.

Change-Id: I5c50e30d003080378cc660dda301150b16f45b72
Closes-Bug: #1445368

commit_message:
Branch update utility

This script was created to rapidly interate through a repo_package file
that contains git sources and set the various repositories inside to
the head of given branch via the SHA. This makes it possible to update
all of the services that we support in an "automated" fashion.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication

Change-Id: Ied01e4968ad7b1b4bd6ecde902bab9e963417358

commit_message:
Removed jsonrpclib dependency

It was used by Arista ML2 driver that is now decomposed from the tree.
The dependency is also one of those blocking our python 3 story [1].

[1]: https://caniusepython3.com/check/ba7f2a23-8a1b-4ec9-9d85-08c7d3b05230

Change-Id: I4de422da14e382ece49987da498d2d7f424e89b4

[{'created': '2015-04-01 10:07:34.000000000', 'message': "Use compatible version of six

Fuel Client uses features of six that appeared
in the version 1.7 but requires a version which
is >= 1.5.2. That causes it to fail if it's installed
to an environment with an old version of six.

This patch changes the version specification to
six>=1.7.0,<=1.9.0 which is compatible with the
Juno release of OpenStack.

Partial-bug: #1439089
Change-Id: Id06ba598df6babe0b5ffcf0a7b08049dbbeaf429

commit_message:
Use compatible versions for requirements

This patch changes the version specification for
the requirements to ones that are compliant with
Juno release of OpenStack.

Partial-bug: #1439089

commit_message:
spec: updates for rspec-puppet 2.x and rspec 3.x

This patch aim to update our specs test in order to work with the rspec-puppet
release 2.0.0, in the mean time, we update rspec syntax order to be prepared
for rspec 3.x move.

In details:
* Upgrade and pin rspec-puppet from 1.0.1 to 2.0.0
* Convert 'should' keyword to 'is_expected.to' (prepare rspec 3.x)
* Fix spec tests for rspec-puppet 2.0.0
* Clean Gemfile (remove over-specificication of runtime deps of
  puppetlabs_spec_helper)

Change-Id: I5eb798ddeebafa2132dfcbd8be37d5cedcfd645f
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Do not check stderr exactly

Some tests rely stderr to much: they either try
to check its content exactly or concider anything
there as a mark of an error which happened.

However, sometimes strerr may contain ocasional
messages from third party components, which leads
to ocasional failures.

This patch fixes the abovementioned issues.

Closes-bug: #1439269
Change-Id: If04b841d63382d379edf656682afdb9abd347372

commit_message:
Add Puppet 4.x lint checks

- This changes the puppet-lint requirement to 1.1.x, so that we can use
  puppet-lint plugins. Most of these plugins are for 4.x compat, but
  some just catch common errors.

Change-Id: I4710484e7481b48ee1c5626d37af6d71278270da
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Separate api and registry packages for Red Hat

Starting in Kilo, Red Hat-based platforms are using separate
glance-api and glance-registry packages (for an example, see
http://trunk.rdoproject.org/f21/current/).

Change-Id: I3ad476846d7dec3ca612e5b0d20b21b8577f4af0

commit_message:
Fix test_set_admin_password_bad_state()

This test was triggering an _instance_update() which waited for 60s on
a non-existent conductor service. Stubbing it out makes the test go
from taking 60s to (basically) 0s.

Change-Id: I412a1b47532be2450743c54aba52fc6e47de90c0

commit_message:
Boot config to deploy containers

This defines environment files which declare a resource type
Heat::InstallConfigAgent.

This can be used by server user_data when booting a pristine
image to install parts to deploy a container with docker-compose
or atomic hook.

This container would then help deploy all other 'docker-compose'
and 'atomic' SoftwareConfig resources.

Example template can be run with downloadable Fedora Atomic Host
image or RHEL Atomic Host, specifically tailored for use
with containers.

https://getfedora.org/cloud/download

Change-Id: Ib5bdcef1111ec9a0bcf588ece277b9328f6e6def

commit_message:
Add sleep_between in live migration scenarios

Main problem when using live migration is running it on a utilized VM.
To simulate this case when benchmarking tester need to spawn a VM that
actually does something. The stressing application may need some time
to spin up. This commit adds configurable sleep_between to live
migration scenarios between booting and live migrating a VM to let
tests wait for eventual stress app to start.

Change-Id: I807d240d93fb42e91e9ce096e328039a6f5d1456

commit_message:
Fix test_attach_interface_failure()

This test was triggering an _instance_update(), which waited for 60s on a
non-existent conductor service. Stubbing it out makes the test go from
taking 60s to (basically) 0s.

Change-Id: Iafc9ff73162d1b767e0ef4b694e187df1714f7e6

commit_message:
Fix test_swap_volume_api_usage()

This test was triggering two attempts to revert the instance task state,
which was making a call to conductor that would never return because
there is no conductor running for this test. Since we were in a save-and-
reraise block, this just got ignored. Thus, this test used to take 120s
purely because it was waiting for two such attempts, at 60s each. Now it
takes (basically) zero time. Yay.

Change-Id: Ibe63cf4c47b3966dc95f70d5a0c9907ae5168264

commit_message:
Proposes Implements RequestSpec object

The former Kilo spec (I5d580c98d98d6899ce46b892d64b21c8dd8abe69) was having a
few problems related to the current select_dests() method and the filter_props
dictionary. Reproposing it for the Liberty timeframe.

Implements blueprint request-spec-object
Previously-Approved: Kilo

Change-Id: Ie8c63a155fe0fce586c39cd4c7da6b81d63c7753
